label.value: increased level of flocculin gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more RNAs transcribed from genes encoding flocculins measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells).

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: increased level of cell wall organization gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more cell wall organization RNAs measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells). Cell wall organization RNAs are transcribed from genes whose products are involved in assembly, alteration, or disassembly of the cell wall.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: decreased histone H3-T3 phosphorylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which phosphorylation of threonine at position 3 of histone H3 is decreased.

label.value: decreased protein localization to centromeric chromatin during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to centromeric chromatin is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to centromeric chromatin during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to centromeric chromatin is decreased during metaphase of mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to centromeric chromatin during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to centromeric chromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type during metaphase of mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased replication fork arrest at MPS1 barrier

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork arrest at the MPS1 barrier in the mating-type locus occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased replication fork arrest at RTS1 barrier

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork arrest at the RTS1 barrier (normally located in the mating-type region) occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased replication fork arrest at tRNA locus

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which replication fork arrest at abnormal replication fork arrest at sites within the eukaryotic tRNA transcription unit occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: normal S-phase DNA damage checkpoint during cellular response to methyl methanesulfonate

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which the S-phase DNA damage checkpoint (also known as the intra-S phase DNA damage checkpoint) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is exposed to methyl methanesulfonate. The S phase DNA damage checkpoint slows progression through S phase in response to DNA damage.

label.value: abnormal dynamic protein localization pattern

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein that is normally dynamically localized to a specific place in the cell shows an abnormal temporal pattern of localization. For example, a protein may move to or from the location more or less frequently than normal.

label.value: abnormal intermittent protein localization to Cdr2 medial cortical node complex

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is normally localized intermittently to the Cdr2 medial cortical node complex shows an abnormal pattern of localization to the complex over time.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: intermittent protein localization to Cdr2 medial cortical node complex decoupled from cell size

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is normally localized intermittently to the Cdr2 medial cortical node complex shows a pattern of localization to the complex over time that is not correlated with cell size as normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein dwell time during intermittent localization to Cdr2 medial cortical node complex

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is normally localized intermittently to the Cdr2 medial cortical node complex is associated with the complex for periods of shorter duration than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein dwell time during intermittent localization to Cdr2 medial cortical node complex

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is normally localized intermittently to the Cdr2 medial cortical node complex is associated with the complex for periods of longer duration than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased frequency of protein localization to Cdr2 medial cortical node complex during intermittent localization to Cdr2 medial cortical node complex

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is normally localized intermittently to the Cdr2 medial cortical node complex is associated with the complex less frequently than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at transcription termination site

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is decreased at sequences that cause RNA polymerase to terminate transcription.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased termination of RNA polymerase II transcription

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the termination of transcription by RNA polymerase II occurs to a lower extent than normal. Termination of all transcripts, or a subset of transcripts, may be affected.

label.value: increased termination of RNA polymerase II transcription

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the termination of transcription by RNA polymerase II occurs to a greater extent than normal. Termination of all transcripts, or a subset of transcripts, may be affected.

label.value: increased cell diameter

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell has a greater diameter (thickness; width) than normal.

label.value: viable vegetative cell with increased cell diameter

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is viable and has a diameter greater than normal. Cell volume may or may not be increased.

label.value: viable elongated vegetative cell with increased cell diameter

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is viable, elongated, and has a greater diameter than normal.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: increased number of Rad52 foci during cellular response to bleomycin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad52 (also called Rad22) accumulates is greater than normal during a cellular response to bleomycin.

definition.value: Because Rad22 often accumulates at double-strand breaks, consider also annotating to 'increased number of double-strand break sites during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000455).

label.value: normal nuclear polyadenylated mRNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of polyadenylated messenger RNA (mRNA) measured in the nucleus is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total mRNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal chromatin organization during recovery from glucose starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which any process of chromatin organization is abnormal when the cell is returned to glucose-rich medium following glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: normal H3-K4 deacetylation during recovery from glucose starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which deacetylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is returned to glucose-rich medium following glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: decreased T-G mismatch DNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of binding to double-stranded DNA containing a G/T mispair by a gene product is decreased, when a gene or the bound DNA sequence is mutated. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: decreased phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate level in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate measured in the plasma membrane is lower than normal.

label.value: increased phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate level in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-3,4,5-trisphosphate measured in the plasma membrane is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate level in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate measured in the plasma membrane is lower than normal.

label.value: increased phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate level in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate measured in the plasma membrane is higher than normal.

label.value: normal phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate level in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate measured in the plasma membrane is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate level in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate measured in the plasma membrane is lower than normal.

label.value: normal phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate level in plasma membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate measured in the plasma membrane is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: inviable elongated tetranucleate aseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable, elongated, has no septum, and contains four nuclei.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal cellular free fatty acid level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more free fatty acids measured in the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased cell length

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which cell length, i.e. the maximum distance between the cell ends, is greater than normal.

definition.value: This term includes both elongated cells, in which both the length and length:diameter ratio are increased relative to wild type, and cells that have increased length but a wild-type length:diameter ratio.

label.value: increased vegetative cell length

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell length, i.e. the maximum distance between the cell ends, is greater than normal.

definition.value: This term includes both elongated cells, in which both the length and length:diameter ratio are increased relative to wild type, and cells that have increased length but a wild-type length:diameter ratio.

label.value: normal protein localization to cell tip during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell tip is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: mislocalized protein distributed in cell cortex

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein is detected abnormally distributed throughout the cell cortex. The protein may normally be restricted to part of the cell cortex, or not normally located in the cell cortex at all.

definition.value: This term can be used for protein that do not normally localize to discrete cytoplasmic regions, or for proteins that do normally show punctate localization but with such localization increased in a mutant. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell cortex of cell tip, with protein distributed in cortex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex of one or both cell tips is decreased, and an increased amount of the protein is instead detected distributed throughout the cell cortex.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to medial cortex, with protein distributed in cell cortex, during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the medial cortex of a cell is decreased, and the protein is instead detected distributed throughout the cell cortex. There may be little or no protein detected at the medial cortex.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal vegetative cell diameter

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell has a normal diameter (thickness; width).

label.value: abnormal protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during anaphase B

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is abnormal during anaphase B of mitosis.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the spindle pole body and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to kinetochore during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during metaphase of mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: mitotic spindle collapse without elongation during metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a short mitotic spindle assembles and elongates during prophase, but does not elongate further and eventually collapses during metaphase.

label.value: decreased protein localization to mitotic spindle midzone, with protein distributed along spindle, during anaphase B

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle midzone is decreased, and some of the protein is present along the entire length of the spindle, during anaphase B of mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to mitotic spindle midzone during metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle midzone during metaphase is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The mitotic spindle midzone is the area in the center of the mitotic spindle where the spindle microtubules from opposite poles overlap.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
